ing driver)|Jim Richards]]<br>{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Mark Skaife]]\n| [[Nissan Skyline R32 GT-R]]\n| rowspan=2 | 161\n|-\n| [[Nissan]] [[Nissan RB engine#RB26DETT|2.6 L]] [[Straight-six engine|S6]] [[Twin-turbo]]\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | [[1992 Tooheys 1000|1992]]\n| rowspan=2 | A\n| rowspan=2 | 1\n| rowspan=2 | Winfield Team Nissan\n| rowspan=2 | {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Mark Skaife]]<br>{{flagicon|NZL}} [[Jim Richards (racing driver)|Jim Richards]]\n| [[Nissan Skyline R32 GT-R]]\n| rowspan=2 | 143\n|-\n| [[Nissan]] [[Nissan RB engine#RB26DETT|2.6 L]] [[Straight-six engine|S6]] [[Twin-turbo]]\n|-\n! colspan=8 | [[V8 Supercars]]\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | [[1999 FAI 1000|1999]]\n| rowspan=2 | \n| rowspan=2 | 7\n| rowspan=2 | Gibson Motorsport\n| rowspan=2 | {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Steven Richards]]<br>{{flagicon|NZL}} [[Greg Murphy]]\n| [[Holden VT Commodore]]\n| rowspan=2 | 161\n|-\n| [[Holden]] 5.0 L [[V8 engine|V8]]\n|}\n\n==Sandown 500 Wins==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Year\n! rowspan=2 | Class\n! rowspan=2 | No\n! rowspan=2 | Team Name\n! rowspan=2 | Drivers\n! Chassis\n! rowspan=2 | Laps\n|-\n! Engine\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | [[1986 Castrol 500|1986]]\n| rowspan=2 | B\n| rowspan=2 | 30\n| rowspan=2 | Peter Jackson Nissan Racing\n| rowspan=2 | {{flagicon|AUS}} [[George Fury]]<br>{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Glenn Seton]]\n| [[Nissan Skyline#RS|Nissan Skyline DR30 RS]]\n| rowspan=2 | 129\n|-\n| [[Nissan]] [[Nissan FJ engine#FJ20E|FJ20E]] 2.0 L [[Inline 4|I4]] [[turbo]]\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | [[1987 Castrol 500|1987]]\n| rowspan=2 | B\n| rowspan=2 | 30\n| rowspan=2 | Peter Jackson Nissan Racing\n| rowspan=2 | {{flagicon|AUS}} [[George Fury]]<br>{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Terry Shiel]]\n| [[Nissan Skyline#RS|Nissan Skyline DR30 RS]]\n| rowspan=2 | 129\n|-\n| [[Nissan]] [[Nissan FJ engine#FJ20E|FJ20E]] 2.0 L [[Inline 4|I4]] [[turbo]]\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | [[1989 .05 \u2013 500|1989]]\n| rowspan=2 | A\n| rowspan=2 | 2\n| rowspan=2 | Nissan Motorsport Australia\n| rowspan=2 | {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Jim Richards (racing driver)|Jim Richards]]<br>{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Mark Skaife]]\n| [[Nissan Skyline HR31 GTS-R]]\n| rowspan=2 | 161\n|-\n| [[Nissan]] [[Nissan RB engine|RB20DET-R]] 2.0 L [[Straight-six engine|S6]] [[turbo]]\n|}\n\n==Other Touring Car Wins==\nOther non-ATCC/AMSCAR race wins by Gibson Motorsport (1981-2003) include:\n\n* [[1983 Australian Endurance Championship|1983 Silastic 300]] at [[Amaroo Park]] - [[George Fury]] ([[Datsun Bluebird 910|Nissan Bluebird Turbo]])\n* 1983 Oran Park 250 at [[Oran Park Raceway]] - George Fury (Nissan Bluebird Turbo)\n* 1983 Berri Fruit Juices Trophy at [[Calder Park Raceway]] ([[1983 Australian Grand Prix]] support race) - George Fury (Nissan Bluebird Turbo)\n* [[1984 Australian Endurance Championship|1984 Silastic 300]] at Amaroo Park - [[Gary Scott (racing driver)|Gary Scott]] (Nissan Bluebird Turbo)\n* [[1984 Australian Grand Prix]] support race at Calder Park Raceway - George Fury (Nissan Bluebird Turbo)\n* [[1986 Australian Endurance Championship|1986 BP Plus 300]] at [[Surfers Paradise International Raceway]] - George Fury and [[Glenn Seton]] ([[Nissan Skyline#RS|Nissan Skyline DR30 RS]])\n* 1986 The Sun South Pacific 300 at Calder Park Raceway - George Fury and Glenn Seton (Nissan Skyline DR30 RS)\n* 1986 Pepsi 250 at Oran Park Raceway - George Fury (Nissan Skyline DR30 RS)\n* [[1987 Yokohama/Bob Jane T-Marts 300]] at Calder Park Raceway / Thunderdome - [[John Bowe (racing driver)|John Bowe]] and [[Terry Shiel]] (Nissan Skyline DR30 RS)\n* 1990 Ansett Air Freight Challenge at [[Adelaide Street Circuit]] ([[1990 Australian Grand Prix]] support race #1) - [[Jim Richards (racing driver)|Jim Richards]] ([[Nissan Skyline R32 GT-R]])\n* 1991 Hush Puppies Olympic Group A Challenge at Adelaide Street Circuit ([[1991 Australian Grand Prix]] support races #1 and #2) - Jim Richards (Nissan Skyline R32 GT-R)\n* 1991 [[Pukekohe 500|Nissan-Mobil 500]] at [[Pukekohe Park Raceway]] ([[New Zealand]]) - Jim Richards and [[Mark Skaife]] (Nissan Skyline R32 GT-R)\n* 1992 Clarks Shoes Group A Finale at Adelaide Street Circuit ([[1992 Australian Grand Prix]] support races #1 and #2) - Jim Richards (Nissan Skyline R32 GT-R)\n\n==Drivers==\nThose who drove for Gibson Motorsport in its many guises in touring car racing during its 22 years of competition from 1981-2003 include (in order of appearance):\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[George Fury]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Fred Gibson (racing driver)|Fred Gibson]]\n* {{flagicon|JPN}} [[Masahiro Hasemi]]\n* {{flagicon|JPN}} [[Kazuyoshi Hoshino]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Fred Gibson (racing driver)#Personal life|Christine Gibson]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Bob Muir (racing driver)|Bob Muir]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Gary Scott (racing driver)|Gary Scott]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Glenn Seton]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Terry Shiel]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Mark Skaife]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[John Bowe (racing driver)|John Bowe]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Grant Jarrett]]\n* {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Anders Olofsson]]\n* {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Jim Richards (racing driver)|Jim Richards]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Garry Waldon]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Drew Price]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Neil Crompton]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[David Brabham]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Colin Bond]]\n* {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Steven Richards]] \n* {{flagicon|GBR}} [[John Cleland (racing driver)|John Cleland]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Darren Hossack]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Steven Ellery]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Darren Pate]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[David Parsons (racing driver)|David Parsons]]\n* {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Simon Wills]]\n* {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Greg Murphy]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[David \"Truckie\" Parsons|David Parsons]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Craig Lowndes]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Rodney Forbes]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Neal Bates]]\n* {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Greg Ritter]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.gibsonmotorsport.com.au/ Gibson Motorsport website]\n