linagh]]\n|\n|}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20150204230832/http://clubgaa.ie/cavan/index.htm Cavan at ClubGAA]\n*[http://cavangaa.ie/ Official Cavan GAA Website]\n\n{{Cavan GAA}}\n{{Cavan Junior Football Championship}}\n\n[[Category:Cavan GAA Football championships]]\n[[Category:Junior Gaelic football county championships]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox GAA tournament\n| name                 = Cavan Junior Football Championship\n| currentlyrunning     = 2019 Cavan Junior Football Championship\n| image                = \n| caption              = \n| irish                = \n| code                 = \n| founded              = 1913\n| abolished            = \n| region               = [[Cavan]], [[Ireland]]\n| trophy               = Se\u00e1n Leddy Cup\n| teams                = 14\n| firstwin             = \n| title holders        = Killinkere\n| currentordinal       = 3\n| super                = rd\n| most titles          = Templeport\n| mostordinal          = 6\n| sponsors             = Cully's Craft Bakery\n| tv                   = \n| motto                = \"The Future is Blue\"\n| website              = http://www.cavangaa.ie\n}}\nThe '''Cavan Junior Football Championship''' is an annual [[Gaelic Athletic Association]] club competition between the third-tier Cavan [[Gaelic football]] clubs. It was first competed for in 1913. The winner qualifies to represent their county in the [[Ulster Junior Club Football Championship|Ulster Club Championship]] and in turn, go on to the [[All-Ireland Junior Club Football Championship]]. The current champions are Killinkere who defeated Shannon Gaels in the 2019 decider.\n\n==Format==\n14 teams will contest the Cully's Craft Bakery Junior Championship.\n\nThe J.F.C. shall be run on a league basis up to the Quarter-Final stage and Knock-out thereafter. Each team will play 4 rounds in the league phase against different opponents with the fixtures decided by a random draw at the conclusion of each round. Placings in the league stage shall be decided in accordance with rule 6.21 of the GAA Official Guide 2016 as amended below:\n\n6.21 (4) If a Championship is partly organised on a League basis, the following Regulations shall apply:\n(a) League Results shall be credited as follows: 2 points for a win, and one for a draw.\n(b) If a Team is Disqualified or Retires during the course of a League Stage, its played games shall stand and its un-played games shall be awarded to the opposing teams.\n(c) As provided for in this Competition Regulation, when teams finish with equal points for Qualification for the Concluding Stages, or for Promotion or Relegation, the tie shall be decided by the following means and in the order specified: (i) Play-Off.\n\nThe top 8 teams in the league progress to the Quarter-Finals. The winner will be promoted to the [[Cavan Intermediate Football Championship]].\n\n==Top winners==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n! style=\"background:blue; color:white; border:1px solid gold;\" |\n! style=\"background:blue; color:white; border:1px solid gold;\" | Team\n! style=\"background:blue; color:white; border:1px solid gold;\" | Wins\n! style=\"background:blue; color:white; border:1px solid gold;\" | Years won\n|-\n| 1\n| Templeport\n| 6\n| 1922, 1923, 1930, 1942, 1968, 2015\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 2\n| [[Castlerahan GAA|Castlerahan]]\n| 5\n| 1951, 1959, 1965, 1987, 1991\n|-\n| Butlersbridge\n| 5\n| 1963, 1974, 2002, 2004, 2009\n|-\n| rowspan=5 | 3\n| Munterconnaught\n| 4\n| 1928, 1949, 1976, 1994\n|-\n| Mountnugent\n| 4\n| 1943, 1964, 1988, 1992\n|-\n| Swanlinbar\n| 4\n| 1985, 1998, 2006, 2010\n|-\n| [[Cornafean GAA|Cornafean]]\n| 4\n| 1914, 1927, 2000, 2016\n|-\n| [[Drumlane GAA|Drumlane]]\n| 4\n| 1948, 1971, 1999, 2018\n|-\n| rowspan=12 | 4\n| [[Ballinagh GAA|Ballinagh]]\n| 3\n| 1913, 1953, 1978\n|-\n| Cavan Slashers\n| 3\n| 1915, 1926, 1938\n|-\n| [[Gowna GFC|Gowna]]\n| 3\n| 1916, 1934, 1982\n|-\n| [[Kingscourt Stars GAA|Kingscourt Stars]]\n| 3\n| 1931, 1954, 1961\n|-\n| Cross\n| 3\n| 1941, 1946, 1962\n|-\n| Drung\n| 3\n| 1947, 1980, 2008\n|-\n| [[Lavey GFC (Cavan)|Lavey]]\n| 3\n| 1950, 1975, 2003\n|-\n| [[Cootehill Celtic GAA|Cootehill]]\n| 3\n| 1952, 1960, 1969\n|-\n| [[Killeshandra GFC|Killeshandra]]\n| 3\n| 1970, 1983, 2007\n|-\n| Kill\n| 3\n| 1986, 1997, 2013\n|-\n| Arva\n| 3\n| 1933, 1993, 2014\n|-\n| Killinkere\n| 2\n| 1956, 1972, 2019\n|-\n| rowspan=7 | 5\n| [[Mullahoran GAA|Mullahoran]]\n| 2\n| 1932, 1940\n|-\n| Croghan\n| 2\n| 1935, 1939\n|-\n| Belturbet\n| 2\n| 1937, 1995\n|-\n| Virginia\n| 2\n| 1958, 1966\n|-\n| Shercock\n| 2\n| 1979, 2011\n|-\n| Knockbride\n| 2\n| 1981, 1996\n|-\n| Ballymachugh\n| 2\n| 1921, 2017\n|-\n| rowspan=21 |6\n| Loughduff Volunteers\n| 1\n| 1917\n|-\n| Drumbo\n| 1\n| 1918\n|-\n| [[Bailieboro Shamrocks GAA|Bailieboro Shamrocks]]\n| 1\n| 1919\n|-\n| Bruskey\n| 1\n| 1920\n|-\n| Tullyco\n| 1\n| 1924\n|-\n| Lurgan\n| 1\n| 1925\n|-\n| Camagh\n| 1\n| 1929\n|-\n| Ballyjamesduff\n| 1\n| 1936\n|-\n| Stradone\n| 1\n| 1944\n|-\n| Annagh\n| 1\n| 1945\n|-\n| Mullagh\n| 1\n| 1955\n|-\n| Cormore\n| 1\n| 1957\n|-\n| Maghera\n| 1\n| 1973\n|-\n| [[Crosserlough GFC|Crosserlough]]\n| 1\n| 1967\n|-\n| Kildallon\n| 1\n| 1977\n|-\n| [[Denn GFC|Denn]]\n| 1\n| 1984\n|-\n| Shannon Gaels\n| 1\n| 1989\n|-\n| [[Killygarry GAA|Killygarry]]\n| 1\n| 1990\n|-\n| [[Drumgoon GFC|Drumgoon]]\n| 1\n| 2001\n|-\n| [[Redhills GFC|Redhills]]\n| 1\n| 2005\n|-\n| [[Laragh United GFC|Laragh United]]\n| 1\n| 2012\n|}\n\n==Roll of honour==\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:silver;\" | '''Year'''\n! style=\"background:silver;\" | '''Winner'''\n! style=\"background:silver;\" | '''Opponent'''\n|-\n| 2019\n| Killinkere 2-16\n| Shannon Gaels 3-08\n|-\n| 2018\n| [[Drumlane GAA|Drumlane]] 0-07, 2-12 (R)\n| Killinkere 0-07, 0-13 (R)\n|-\n| 2017\n| Ballymachugh 2-11\n| [[Drumalee GFC|Drumalee]] 0-13\n|-\n| [[2016 Cavan Junior Football Championship|2016]]\n| [[Cornafean GAA|Cornafean]] 1-16\n| Ballymachugh 0-11\n|-\n| [[2015 Cavan Junio