{"title_page": "Mad River Mountain", "text_new": "{{short description|Ski resort in Ohio, US}}\n{{Infobox ski area\n |name=Mad River Mountain\n |logo=Madrivermountain.png\n |picture=Mad River Mountain and Valley Hi.jpg|\n |caption=Aerial view of Mad River Mountain from the east\n |location=[[Valley Hi, Ohio]] ([[Jefferson Township, Logan County, Ohio]])\n |nearest_city=[[Bellefontaine, Ohio]]\n |coordinates = {{coord|40|18|58.74|N|83|40|50.03|W|type:landmark_scale:50000|display=inline}}\n |top_elevation={{convert|1460|ft|m}}<ref name=\"skisite\">''SkiSite'': [http://www.skisite.com/downhillDetail.cfm?id=682 Mad River Mountain]</ref>\n |base_elevation={{convert|1160|ft|m}}<ref name=\"skisite\"/>\n |skiable_area={{convert|144|acre|km2}}<ref name=\"onthesnow\">''OnTheSnow.com'': [http://www.onthesnow.com/ohio/mad-river-mountain/profile.html Mad River Overview]</ref>\n |number_trails=23<ref name=\"skisite\"/>\n |longest_run={{convert|.5|mi|km}}<ref name=\"onthesnow\"/>\n |liftsystem=12<ref name=\"rsn\">''[[Regional Sports Network|RSN]]'': [http://www.rsn.com/Resorts/Mad_River_Mountain Mad River Mountain] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081019022606/http://www.rsn.com/Resorts/Mad_River_Mountain |date=2008-10-19 }}</ref>\n |snowfall={{convert|36|in|cm}}<ref name=\"skisite\"/>\n |external_link=[http://www.skimadriver.com/ SkiMadRiver.com]\n |}}\n'''Mad River Mountain''' is a [[ski]] and [[snowboard]] [[Ski resort|resort]] in [[Valley Hi, Ohio|Valley Hi]], [[Ohio]], [[United States]]. The elevation of Mad River Mountain is {{convert|1460|ft|m}} with a vertical drop of {{convert|300|ft|m|abbr=on}}, and it has a ski season that runs from December 1 through March 16.<ref name=\"skisite\"/> The resort, which opened in 1962, as Valley Hi Ski Area,<ref name=\"onthesnow\"/> is owned and operated by [[Vail Associates]].\n\nThere are 23 trails of various skill levels, a [[Tubing (recreation)#Snow|tubing]] park, three terrain parks, and two beginner areas. Of the resort's 12 total lifts, there are 6 surface lifts, 6 chair lifts, and 1 fixed quad lift.<ref name=\"rsn\"/> Since the annual natural snowfall averages only {{convert|36|in|cm}}, Mad River Mountain has the largest snow making system in Ohio, with 130 [[snow cannon]]s that cover 100% of the trails.<ref name=\"skisite\"/>\n\nThe resort lies off [[U.S. Route 33]] east of the city of [[Bellefontaine, Ohio|Bellefontaine]].  It is located {{convert|6|mi|km}} southeast of [[Campbell Hill (Ohio)|Campbell Hill]], Ohio's highest point, and it is near the source of the [[Mad River (Ohio)|Mad River]]. The resort's iconic bar venue called 'The Loft' caught fire on September 16, 2015, and was considered a total loss.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Zachariah|first1=Holly|title=Investigators search for cause of Mad River ski lodge fire|url=http://www.dispatch.com/content/stories/local/2015/09/16/mad-river-mountain-fire.html|accessdate=17 September 2015|work=Columbus Dispatch|date=17 September 2015}}</ref> Local firm Thomas & Marker Construction was chosen to prepare the resort for the 2015-2016 winter season. The site was demolished and temporary structures were erected October 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Blog {{!}} SkiMadRiver.com|url = http://skimadriver.com/blog.html?id=183|website = skimadriver.com|accessdate = 2015-10-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Construction underway for new lodge at Mad River Mountain|url = http://wdtn.com/2015/10/19/construction-underway-for-new-lodge-at-mad-river-mountain/|website = WDTN|accessdate = 2015-10-24|first = Paul|last = Rodzinka}}</ref> A new lodge has been constructed and is in its final stages for the 2016-2017 season. Mad River Mountain proudly shows off its new $6.5M lodge which they claim will draw many customers back for the upcoming season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.springfieldnewssun.com/news/local/new-lodge-mad-river-mountain-almost-complete-after-fire/D4Hwc2nUg7KOsukbNosaPN/|website=SpringfieldNewsSun.com|title=New $6.5M lodge at Mad River Mountain almost complete after fire}}</ref>\n\n==Notable Employees==\nIn the early 1980s [[Olympic Games|Olympic]] [[medalist]] [[Putzi Frandl]] was employed as a [[ski school|ski instructor]] at the resort.<ref>Bellefontaine Examiner, Olympic Skier at MRM January 13, 1983</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://justformyboys.blogspot.com/2011/04/my-famous-friend.html|title=My Famous Friend|publisher=http://justformyboys.blogspot.com|date=2011-04-29}}</ref> Louie Vito, Olympic snowboard medalist got his start at Mad River Mountain, and sponsors a food drive for a local pantry each year.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.skimadriver.com/ Mad River Mountain]\n\n[[Category:Ski areas and resorts in Ohio]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Logan County, Ohio]]\n[[Category:Peak Resorts]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Logan County, Ohio]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Ski resort in Ohio, US}}\n{{Infobox ski area\n |name=Mad River Mountain\n |logo=Madrivermountain.png\n |picture=Mad River Mountain and Valley Hi.jpg|\n |caption=Aerial view of Mad River Mountain from the east\n |location=[[Valley Hi, Ohio]] ([[Jefferson Township, Logan County, Ohio]])\n |nearest_city=[[Bellefontaine, Ohio]]\n |coordinates = {{coord|40|18|58.74|N|83|40|50.03|W|type:landmark_scale:50000|display=inline}}\n |top_elevation={{convert|1460|ft|m}}<ref name=\"skisite\">''SkiSite'': [http://www.skisite.com/downhillDetail.cfm?id=682 Mad River Mountain]</ref>\n |base_elevation={{convert|1160|ft|m}}<ref name=\"skisite\"/>\n |skiable_area={{convert|144|acre|km2}}<ref name=\"onthesnow\">''OnTheSnow.com'': [http://www.onthesnow.com/ohio/mad-river-mountain/profile.html Mad River Overview]</ref>\n |number_trails=23<ref name=\"skisite\"/>\n |longest_run={{convert|.5|mi|km}}<ref name=\"onthesnow\"/>\n |liftsystem=12<ref name=\"rsn\">''[[Regional Sports Network|RSN]]'': [http://www.rsn.com/Resorts/Mad_River_Mountain Mad River Mountain] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081019022606/http://www.rsn.com/Resorts/Mad_River_Mountain |date=2008-10-19 }}</ref>\n |snowfall={{convert|36|in|cm}}<ref name=\"skisite\"/>\n |external_link=[http://www.skimadriver.com/ SkiMadRiver.com]\n |}}\n'''Mad River Mountain''' is a [[ski]] and [[snowboard]] [[Ski resort|resort]] in [[Valley Hi, Ohio|Valley Hi]], [[Ohio]], [[United States]]. The elevation of Mad River Mountain is {{convert|1460|ft|m}} with a vertical drop of {{convert|300|ft|m|abbr=on}}, and it has a ski season that runs from December 1 through March 16.<ref name=\"skisite\"/> The resort, which opened in 1962, as Valley Hi Ski Area,<ref name=\"onthesnow\"/> is owned and operated by [[Vail Associates]].\n\nThere are 23 trails of various skill levels, a [[Tubing (recreation)#Snow|tubing]] park, three terrain parks, and two beginner areas. Of the resort's 12 total lifts, there are 6 surface lifts, 6 chair lifts, and 1 fixed quad lift.<ref name=\"rsn\"/> Since the annual natural snowfall averages only {{convert|36|in|cm}}, Mad River Mountain has the largest snow making system in Ohio, with 130 [[snow cannon]]s that cover all of its trails.<ref name=\"skisite\"/>\n\nThe resort lies off [[U.S. Route 33]] east of the city of [[Bellefontaine, Ohio|Bellefontaine]].  It is located {{convert|6|mi|km}} southeast of [[Campbell Hill (Ohio)|Campbell Hill]], Ohio's highest point, and it is near the source of the [[Mad River (Ohio)|Mad River]]. The resort's iconic bar venue called 'The Loft' caught fire on September 16, 2015, and was considered a total loss.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Zachariah|first1=Holly|title=Investigators search for cause of Mad River ski lodge fire|url=http://www.dispatch.com/content/stories/local/2015/09/16/mad-river-mountain-fire.html|accessdate=17 September 2015|work=Columbus Dispatch|date=17 September 2015}}</ref> Local firm Thomas & Marker Construction was chosen to prepare the resort for the 2015-2016 winter season. The site was demolished and temporary structures were erected in October 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Blog {{!}} SkiMadRiver.com|url = http://skimadriver.com/blog.html?id=183|website = skimadriver.com|accessdate = 2015-10-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Construction underway for new lodge at Mad River Mountain|url = http://wdtn.com/2015/10/19/construction-underway-for-new-lodge-at-mad-river-mountain/|website = WDTN|accessdate = 2015-10-24|first = Paul|last = Rodzinka}}</ref> A new lodge has been constructed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.springfieldnewssun.com/news/local/new-lodge-mad-river-mountain-almost-complete-after-fire/D4Hwc2nUg7KOsukbNosaPN/|website=SpringfieldNewsSun.com|title=New $6.5M lodge at Mad River Mountain almost complete after fire}}</ref>\n\n==Notable Employees==\nIn the early 1980s [[Olympic Games|Olympic]] [[medalist]] [[Putzi Frandl]] was employed as a [[ski school|ski instructor]] at the resort.<ref>Bellefontaine Examiner, Olympic Skier at MRM January 13, 1983</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://justformyboys.blogspot.com/2011/04/my-famous-friend.html|title=My Famous Friend|publisher=http://justformyboys.blogspot.com|date=2011-04-29}}</ref> Louie Vito, Olympic snowboard medalist got his start at Mad River Mountain, and sponsors a food drive for a local pantry each year.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.skimadriver.com/ Mad River Mountain]\n\n[[Category:Ski areas and resorts in Ohio]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Logan County, Ohio]]\n[[Category:Peak Resorts]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Logan County, Ohio]]\n", "name_user": "5.153.218.57", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(more info)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mad_River_Mountain"}
